<title>USA: Boston Beer Co Inc Q3 net rises.</title>
<headline>Boston Beer Co Inc Q3 net rises.</headline>
<dateline>BOSTON 1996-10-22</dateline>
<text>
<p>(In thousands, except per share data)</p>
<p>				3 Months Ended	9 Months Ended</p>
<p>			   Sep 28,	Sep 30  Sep 28,     Sep 30,</p>
<p>				1996	 1995	1996	 1995</p>
<p> Barrels sold		294	   246   913(A)	   688</p>
<p> Gross sales	   $51,598     $44,512 $160,457    $121,894</p>
<p> Operating income	3,691	 2,408   11,742	 7,427</p>
<p> Net income		2,296  1,828(B,C)    7,297  4,702(B,C)</p>
<p> Shr			  0.11   0.10(B,C)     0.36   0.26(B,C)</p>
<p> Avg shrs		 20,427   17,949(C)   20,397   17,949(C)</p>
<p>Notes: (A): Includes an additional 2,000 barrels shipped, but not reported in the second quarter 1996.</p>
<p>(B): Includes a non-recurring gain of $807,000 ($0.02 per share after taxes) related to the sale of certain distribution rights to a major metropolitan area.</p>
<p>(C): Pro forma data for the quarter ended September 30, 1995 is presented to reflect the recapitalization of the company in conjunction with its initial public offering, on November 20, 1995, which resulted in the issuance of 3,109,279 shares of Common Stock and a change in the tax status of the entity from a partnership to a corporation.  </p>
<p>Orders for October/November 1996 exceeded shipments for October/November 1995 by 5.5 pct.</p>
</text>
